# Description

This is an agent for proofreading comments in Rust source code files.

It is slightly more optimized for the Rust version compared to the `proof-comments.devai` version. For instance, at the end, we have a `text::ensure_single_ending_newline(content);` to ensure each Rust file ends with a single newline, as per Rust convention (something LLMs often overlook).

# Data

```rhai

// Notes:
//   - input: This is the FileRef (with .path, .name, .stem, .ext) for each file matching the -f glob.
//   - file::load(input.path) will return a FileRecord, adding .content for the content of the file.
//   - In Rhai, to return a dictionary/object, use the notation #{ name: value, â€¦ }.

return #{
    file: file::load(input.path)
};
```

# Instruction

For the following Rust file:

{{data.file.path}}

```
{{data.file.content}}
```

- Correct the English of all comments if it is a code base (do not correct the code).
- Correct the English of all content if it is a Markdown file.
- Only correct comments if necessary.
- Preserve the whitespace (do not change tabs into spaces and vice versa).
- Return the corrected content without any explanation.

# Output

```rhai
// Note: LLMs often, but not always, return a code block for the result. 
//       The md::outer_block_content_or_raw function will get the content between the first 
//       and last triple backticks or return ai_output if there are no triple backticks.
let content = md::outer_block_content_or_raw(ai_output);
// Ensure the content ends with exactly one newline
let content = text::ensure_single_ending_newline(content);

// Example of how to save to the same file
file::save(data.file.path, content);

// This will be printed by devai if it is a string
return "File processed: " + data.file.path
```